    <html:body xmlns='data:,wayscript.bit' xmlns:html='http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml'
          xmlns:step='data:,wayscript.bit.step'>
        <html:h1>Moral forms</html:h1>



<postulate id='FW'>
    My will is rational only insofar as I presuppose my freedom to act
    <step:script>
        Script this, <html:a href='http://reluk.ca/project/100-0/poll/c/pipe/100-5/norm.xht#F-b'>
        borrowing from Kant</html:a>
        </step:script>
    </postulate>



<moral_forms>
    <html:a way:join='/moral_facts.xht#M'>Moral matter M</html:a> has two essential forms
    <way:group> comprising:
        <G id='G'>Relation of the personal to the endmost goal of the person</G>
          <!-- changing?  sync'd → http://reluk.ca/project/proto-wayic/architec/form_G  HERE CUSTOM -->
        <F id='F'>Promotion of a maximum, universal sum of personal freedom</F>
          <!-- changing?  sync'd → http://reluk.ca/project/proto-wayic/architec/form_F  HERE CUSTOM -->
        </way:group>
    <formal_necessity id='formal_necessity'>
        Apparently G and F are formally necessary to M
        <_>
            Form G thoroughly entangles M
            <step:script>Script this</step:script>
            </_>
        <_>
            Form F thoroughly entangles M
            <step:script>Script this</step:script>
            </_>
        </formal_necessity>
    <instrumental_fitness id='instrumental_fitness'>
        Apparently G and F are instrumentally necessary and sufficient to M
        <_>
            M is aimed at E
            <M way:join='/moral_facts.xht#M'/>
            <E way:join='/moral_facts.xht#E'/>
            </_>
        <_ id='E_from_GF'>
            To reach E, it appears necessary and sufficient to institute G and F
            <way:group> comprising:
                <_>Instituting G seems prudently indispensible as a means to E</_>
                <_>Instituting F seems prudently indispensible as a means to E</_>
                <_>The combined institution of G and F seems to lack nothing as a means to E</_>
                </way:group>
            <step:script>Script this</step:script>
            </_>
        </instrumental_fitness>



    </moral_forms>



